<h2>Missouri Incentives & Rebates</h2>
<p>Missouri offers a comprehensive array of incentives that significantly reduce the cost of solar panel and HVAC system installations. The federal Investment Tax Credit (ITC) remains the most substantial incentive, providing a 30% tax credit for solar installations through 2032. This credit applies to the total system cost, including equipment, installation, and associated electrical work. For a typical \$20,000 solar installation, the federal credit provides \$6,000 in tax savings, which can be carried forward if it exceeds current tax liability.</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Federal 30% Solar Tax Credit:</strong> Available through 2032, this credit covers the entire cost of solar panel systems, inverters, mounting equipment, and installation labor. The credit can be applied against federal income taxes and unused portions can be carried forward to subsequent tax years. For battery storage systems installed with solar, the credit also applies to the storage component.</li>
<li><strong>Property Tax Exemption:</strong> Missouri provides a complete property tax exemption for solar energy systems, ensuring that the added home value from solar installation doesn't increase property tax obligations. This exemption applies to both residential and commercial installations and remains in effect for the life of the system.</li>
<li><strong>Ameren Missouri Programs:</strong> The state's largest utility offers rebates up to \$500 for ENERGY STAR certified HVAC systems and provides net metering for solar customers at retail rates. Ameren's Residential Energy Efficiency Programs include rebates for high-efficiency heat pumps, smart thermostats, and whole-home energy audits.</li>
<li><strong>Local Utility Rebates:</strong> Municipal utilities and electric cooperatives throughout Missouri offer additional rebates. City Utilities in Springfield provides up to \$400 for high-efficiency heat pumps, while Kansas City Power & Light offers rebates for smart thermostats and HVAC tune-ups.</li>
<li><strong>Maximizing Incentives:</strong> To optimize savings, homeowners should coordinate timing of solar and HVAC installations to capture all available rebates and credits. Working with certified contractors ensures proper documentation for incentive claims and compliance with program requirements.</li>
</ul>

